<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
List your reason(or comments) why Dire charm (needs to be)and will be nerfed,mine are:<P>1.The refresh time is barelly over 1 hr (real time)and the cost to attain this incredible skill is fairly easy to get (relativelly speaking).<P>2.This will make us (enchanters)the best pet class (yes including epic mages)even though we are not a true pet class. An obvious design flaw.<P>3.This will radically change high lvl enchanter class by making us the best soloer in the game by a large margin(at least now we have some sort of competition).<P>4.This will unbalence some epic encounters (that VI cherish) so much and make them instead pushover mobs.They put in safeguards for tov/vp/sky ect but many zones are still available for the picking.<P>5.Nothing else,for any class,approaches being this good.(although duids/necros get the ghetto version)<P>6.It will make the duo combination enchanter cleric silly powerful.The efficiency of CH on mob pets approaches the ridiculous,hasnt VI learned from AoW incident?<P>7.It will make many lewt that is designed specifically  to be available for groups only, attainable by a solo enchanter.(VI really hate this)<P>8.This tool will make power levelling incredibly powerfull.<P>9.Some enchanter will either unententionally or maliciously  perma charm a PH for a named mob thus preventing his spawn on a permanent  basis.<P>10. Finally,it's too good to be true, the classic sign of something that is game unbalancing. <P>I think VI should take a  really good look at it now that hopefully none has it,instead of waiting for us to work to get it,enjoy it and then nerf it beyond belief.<P>Saltino<BR>Phantasmist<P>Edit: added number 9 to the list.
</FONT>
