<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, since no one has it yet, I can't even begin to hypothesize how overpowering this will be.  The one thing I noticed is that they changed the text of the skill.  It used to say it gave a chance of permanently charming something which led me to believe that there would be a certain percentage of the time it would be a permanent charm.  However, the text now reads (with Druid in the place of Enchanter):<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>This ability allows the Druid to charm an NPC without fear that the NPC will break the charm (charm will end only when the Druid leaves the zone or logs out) without the memorization of a spell or the expenditure of mana.  All of the usual restriction for charm spells apply to this ability as well, except in regards to duration.  The Refresh Timer for this ability is 72 minutes (one day of game time).<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I just know I'm not going to put any points into this until other people have it.  I don't have to spend 9 points on something that might get nerfed into uselessness.  *shrug* I suppose we just have to wait and see...<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=43477" TARGET=_blank>Cantatus</A> of The Haven<BR>Karana Server<BR><I>"Ego sum callidior quam tu quod possum legere hoc."</I>
