You mean... enchanters will get to contribute actual output in XP groups other than being a buff monkey?!<P>...harish the thought...<P>Quite frankly in a high level zone its difficult to find something to DICTATE let alone a level 49 cap (if it even is 49, noone knows this yet). Your solo power would increase, yes, but if you think somone is gonna solo deep sebilis with this without backup all you're lookin' at is a whole lotta CR time.<P>First off assuming this is a level 49 cap, lets assume you want to use this in sebby as well.<P>No, you cannot permacharm a Krup or Illis or R33t. You can't even charm a bok reliably. You are limmited pretty much to Zols and therabouts.<P>Even a hasted Zol will get it's ass kicked by two slowed krups. Even if you could keep the pulls down to 2 per attempt, a chanter does not have snare, and all it takes is one lucky gater or runner. Mez the Krup? sure ya could. Resist? YOUR F--KED!! No healing available on a frog thats already pissed from the slow attempt, nowhere to run, etc etc.<P>Sure it can be pulled off... but it would take a lot of control and skill, and even then the biggest thing you could possibly solo would probably be Pyra or ZO. Wooptedo!<P>Really unless you spend a whole lotta time in guk I don't see this as overpowered at all. The charm cap is simply too low to come close to that.<P>And we still don't know how badly this spell can resist. Keep in mind, resist = 72 minute downtime, or resorting to a more dangerous random charm till it pops again.<P>The dire charm for necros essentially can *possibly* allow one to solo in HS somewhere. Again, this is extremely dangerous especially with so many harmtouchers, and the necro has no way of really augmenting the pet itself (though they can slow now) to skew the advantage. Keep in mind on your average necro... two HTs and its pretty much all over.<P>Druids? Ph34r the griffon! Wooo.<P>*smirks*
