<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Thing is, that Jabober pet actually taunts.<P>I have never been able to get my charmed pets to taunt (I don't get the 'Attacking target master' message). If there isn't anyone else to taunt the mob usually just ignores my charmed pet and comes for me.<P>One of my favourite exp places is chef in Sebilis. I usually charm one of the boks/krups (yeah, a krup depending on how much I trust my cleric =]) and keep that charmed for the whole duration, recharming as it breaks, etc.<P>Point is, if I send my pet to attack a just pulled mob without giving the tanks at least a few hits to build aggro, the mob comes directly for me and gives me a few whacks before going after the tanks.<P>Of course, in this group situation there IS a taunter, so my pet not taunting doesn't really matter.<P>In solo situations, or where you don't have a taunter, root works quite nicely. It will force the mob to beat on the nearest target (your pet), and while its rooted, your pet's hits will build the aggro. Once root wears off, it should hopefully have enough aggro to stay on your pet.<P>--------------------<P>Falon Van`yer, 59 Enchanter<BR>Ethaniel Van`yer, 52 Warrior<BR>Forged Souls<BR>The Seventh Hammer
