Falon  no answers here as to the mechanics of Dire charm ,at this point enchanters are reduced to speculations till 1 of us actually get the skill (wich should be very soon,there is got to be a Power-exp enchanter out there that's gonna do it in a matter of days).<P>As far as the taunting: The main concern with charmed mobs is the initial attack impact,this is the danger spot where the hostile mob might just ignore the pet and head straight for you.Our animation does a fine job at taunting, a charmed pet however has a nice "natural" ability to taunt wich is pure damage that much larger than our animation.<BR>So no taunt yes, but the large damage makes up for it.<BR>There is only the initial window of a few seconds to deal with after that the hostile mob should be stuck on your charmed mob.A nice way to deal with it is as you yourself noted :root initially till pet builds aggro.<BR>Another way that might do is our new add/substract aggro spells Once that is done only mind the additional agro generated by:<BR>1.Being too close to the hostile mob.<BR>2. Sitting within a certain radius.<BR>4.Generating additional aggro with debuffs ect..<BR>5.Low health <P>saltino<BR>Phantasmist
