Dire charm will be awesome in xp groups. When finishing off level 59 and getting some buffer 60 xp, I was charming krups in seb using boltran's. I would keep bedlam up on myself, and stun/stun/recharm if it broke. Worked like a charm, and if the cleric was good I hasted him and he was doing more damage than everyone but a epic rogue...<P>Get a krup or sebilite guardian, buff it with VoG/strength/whatever, it becomes a machine. Enchanter become the second most damaging class (in melee) in the game, the best crowd control, and the best soloers in some places.<P>It will own in xp groups, but I don't think it will have a significant effect on raids...I can't think of a single 49- mob that would make or break a raid in velious (might help a little on trak type encounters). It will not be able to hold agro with the pet changes, it will not be able to put out more damage then well equiped anything (puts out more than reg 53-57 seb warriors, but doesn't come close to primal or even exquisite/epic weapon damage output).<P>It will not throw off the game balance, but it will make 59+ enchanters with it a huge asset (like they weren't already heh) in xp groups not only for crowd control, but for damage also. <P>Camedil Chaosweaver<BR>Phantasmist<BR>Innoruuk Server
