Dire Charm is not really as overpowered as you claim to be unless the charm lvl cap is very high. If you have the charm staff from VP, you pretty much have perma charm. I have yet fail to see it to be over powered, in raids or exp group because the lvl cap is like 49ish. While a 7-8k hp quad 127+ pet is nice, it by no means is overpowered. Pet, me + a healer get about same exp as a decent equiped monk/warr soloing. <P>You have to be able to charm 55+ mobs to really have overpowered perma pet and only a chance at that, which is another reason why it might not be overpowered( if the chance is only 10% or less ). <P>There are always some exceptions in certain zones with mobs that hit much higher then their lvl indicates. But you don't just claim the skill to be overpowered because of those exceptions, just like you don't nerf charm as regard to certain quad hitting, flurry npc in Kael, you nerf the NPC.
