dire charm is a nerf waiting to happen.  the question is how to nerf it.<P>1.  level 35 (or so) limit.  since mostly 60th chars get it, this would make it utterly useless in practice since there are no 35th level mobs in high level zones but verant could still say its a good skill.<P>2.  no buffs or heals for these pets.  this would hurts druids more than chanters.  we can get wizzie/cleric pets.  we can also just use them every other fight if nessesary.<P>3.  nerf the mob as soon as it is charmed.  nerf hp to 2k and damage to 60 max.  make it just less than mage epic.  mages still will be mad.<P>4.  super resist rate.  if nobody can actually charm one, no nerf required.<P>5.  add a time limit.  maybe 8 minutes fixed then attack the chanter or just poof the pet.<P>6.  just delete the skill, sorry about all the points you put into it.  no reenbursments.<P>im betting both 1 and 2.  i admit verant has a long history of taking the easy way out and that would be 6.
